'''Guéla Maho Lewis Doué''' (born 17 October 2002) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Club career==

=== Rennes ===
Having joined [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] as an eight year old,<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last= |first= |date=17 Jan 2023 |title=Guéla Doué prolonge jusqu'en 2025 |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-guela-doue-prolonge-jusqu-en-2025-aa857f5c-9696-11ed-a0e2-3c14145668d8 |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Le Goff |first=Brian |date=18 Jan 2023 |title=Stade Rennais : le grand frère d'un joueur des Rouge et Noir prolonge son contrat |url=https://actu.fr/bretagne/rennes_35238/stade-rennais-le-petit-frere-d-un-joueur-des-rouge-et-noir-prolonge-son-contrat_56678076.html |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Actu Rennes |publisher={{ill|actu.fr|fr}} |language=fr}}</ref> Guéla Doué was part of a 2002 generation comprising the likes of [[Eduardo Camavinga]], [[Brandon Soppy]] and [[Georginio Rutter]].<ref name=":1" /> He began playing with Rennes [[Championnat National 3|National 3]] reserves in [[2020–21 Championnat National 3|2020–21]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |date=2021-11-18 |title=Stade Rennais. Premier contrat pro pour le jeune latéral droit Guéla Doué |url=https://www.letelegramme.fr/football/stade-rennais/premier-contrat-pro-pour-le-jeune-lateral-droit-guela-doue-18-11-2021-12870022.php |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=[[Le Télégramme]] |language=fr}}</ref>

The young [[Defender (association football)|defender]] signed his first professional contract with the club on 18 November 2021.<ref name=":3">{{Cite news |last= |first= |date=18 November 2021 |title=Guela Doué signe son premier contrat professionnel |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-guela-doue-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel-09323b6e-488a-11ec-8077-d5a3bbe4241e |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref><ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rault |first=Mathieu |date=18 Nov 2021 |title=Stade Rennais : Guéla Doué passe pro |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a1465759867863624737-stade-rennais-guela-doue-passe-pro |access-date=2 February 2023 |website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}}}}</ref> His progress through the [[2021–22 Stade Rennais F.C. season|2021–22 season]] was however halted by a serious injury,<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rassouli |first=Thomas |title=Pierre-Emmanuel Bourdeau : " On ne veut pas former des équipes, mais des joueurs d'équipe " |url=https://www.stade-rennais-online.com/ENTRETIEN-Pierre-Emmanuel-Bourdeau-On-ne-veut-pas-former-des-equipes-mais-des.html |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=SRO |language=fr}}</ref> making his way back with the reserve only in May 2022, still managing to help them winning promotion to the [[2022–23 Championnat National 2|National 2]] after only narrowly topping the [[2021–22 Championnat National 3#Group K: Brittany|Brittany group]].<ref>{{Cite news |last= |first= |date=28 May 2022 |title=N3 : le Stade Rennais maintient la pression après sa victoire face à Plouzané |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/foot-amateur/football-n3-le-stade-rennais-maintient-la-pression-apres-sa-victoire-face-a-plouzane-ca861c00-dec0-11ec-8004-b79acaead9a5 |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sermaise |first=Florian |date=2022-06-04 |title=Le Stade Rennais valide sa montée en N2 après un match fou ! |url=https://www.foot-national.com/national-3/le-stade-rennais-valide-sa-montee-en-n2-apres-un-match-fou--779889 |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Foot National |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Guyon |first=Pierre |date=4 June 2022 |title=L'équipe réserve arrache la montée en National 2 |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-l-equipe-reserve-arrache-la-montee-en-national-2-dc7a76fa-e42d-11ec-a695-df7df0a2b6df |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref>

Doué made his first team debut during the [[2022–23 Stade Rennais F.C. season#Pre-season and friendlies|2022 summer friendlies]], joining his brother [[Désiré Doué|Désiré]] on the field against [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fretigné |first=Laurent |date=23 Jul 2022 |title=Guéla et Désiré Doué, deux frangins qui portent bien leur nom |language=fr |work=Ouest-France |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-guela-et-desire-doue-deux-frangins-qui-portent-bien-leur-nom-68c539fa-09e1-11ed-89ff-d7b4632af60c |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref>

Having already appeared several times on the bench in [[2022–23 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] under [[Bruno Génésio]]'s management, on 17 January 2023 Guéla extended his contract with the club until 2025.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last1=Quarez |first1=Benjamin |date=17 January 2023 |title=Ligue 1 : Rennes prolonge Guéla Doué jusqu'en 2025 |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1-rennes-prolonge-guela-doue-jusquen-2025-17-01-2023-H5UEYAGMJZBLFIFXOSGLZ6HNGE.php |access-date=2 February 2023 |website=[[Le Parisien]]}}</ref><ref name=":4" />

He made his senior debut with [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] in a 3–0 league win over [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] on 1 February 2023, coming in as a late substitute for his younger brother, who had just became the youngest ever player to deliver an assist and score a goal in a [[Ligue 1]] game.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lejolivet |first=Pierre |date=1 Feb 2023 |title=Désiré Doué bat un record de précocité contre Strasbourg |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-desire-doue-bat-un-record-de-precocite-contre-strasbourg-25f3760c-a278-11ed-92f2-333ccb208462 |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Brosse |first=Raphaël |date=2 February 2023 |title=Records de précoces, gloire à Juninho, Balogun devant Mbappé : les tops et flops de la 21e journée |url=https://www.eurosport.fr/football/ligue-1/2021-2022/ligue-1-records-de-precoces-gloire-a-juninho-balogun-devant-mbappe-les-tops-et-flops-de-la-21e-journ_sto9366061/story.shtml |access-date=2 February 2023 |website=[[Eurosport]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Le Gall |first=Pierre |date=1 Feb 2023 |title=Stade Rennais – Strasbourg. Le réveil éclatant d'Amine Gouiri : les notes des Rouge et Noir |language=fr |work=[[Ouest-France]] |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/stade-rennais/stade-rennais-strasbourg-le-reveil-eclatant-d-amine-gouiri-les-notes-des-rouge-et-noir-026e5496-a27c-11ed-92f2-333ccb208462 |access-date=2 Feb 2023}}</ref>

=== Strasbourg ===
On 26 July 2024, Doué joined [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] by signing a contract until 2029.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr/guela-doue-au-racing/ |title=Guela Doué au Racing |publisher=RC Strasbourg Alsace |language=fr |date=26 July 2024 }}</ref> On 18 August, he made his debut in the Ligue 1 opener against [[Montpellier HSC]], which ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-18 |title=Multiplex Ligue 1: Lens s'impose à Angers, le MHSC et le RCSA se maîtrisent, le TFC et Nantes aussi |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/direct-multiplex-ligue-1-suivez-montpellier-strasbourg-toulouse-nantes-et-angers-lens-en-live_LS-202408180184.html |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr}}</ref> On 9 November, he scored the first goal of his professional career in a 1–3 defeat against [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-09 |title=Strasbourg-Monaco : victoire des Monégasques qui s'emparent de la deuxième place du championnat |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/direct-strasbourg-monaco-suivez-en-live-le-match-de-la-11e-journee-de-ligue-1_LS-202411090290.html |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Doué was born in France, to an Ivorian father and French mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koaci.com/article/2024/08/02/cote-divoire/sport/cote-divoire-lelephant-guela-doue-reste-finalement-en-france-et-sengage-au-rc-strasbourg-jusquen-2029_179938.html|title=Côte d'Ivoire : L'éléphant Guela Doué reste finalement en France et s'engage au RC Strasbourg jusqu'en 2029|website=KOACI}}</ref> He holds dual-citizenship and holds [[Ivorian nationality law|Ivorian]] by descent.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mercato : le Franco-ivoirien Guéla Doué prolonge à Rennes jusqu'en 2025 |url=https://www.ami-sportif.com/2023/01/18/mercato-le-franco-ivoirien-guela-doue-prolonge-a-rennes-jusquen-2025/ |access-date=2 February 2023 |website=ami-sportif.com}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast U23]]s for a set of matches in March 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stade-rennais-online.com/+Selections-Guela-Doue-appele-avec-la-Cote-d-Ivoire-U23+.html|title=Sélections : Guela Doué appelé avec la Côte d'Ivoire U23|website=Stade Rennais Online}}</ref>

Doué made his debut for the senior [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]] on 23 March 2024 in a friendly against [[Benin national football team|Benin]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-23 |title=La Côte d'Ivoire et le Bénin dos à dos en amical |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/La-cote-d-ivoire-et-le-benin-dos-a-dos-en-amical/1456422 |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

Three days later, he scored his first national team goal, the winner in the 84th minute in a 2–1 friendly victory over Uruguay.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/699348/uruguay-ivory-coast|title=Ivory Coast v Uruguay game report|date=26 March 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-27 |title=La Côte d'Ivoire et Guéla Doué éteignent l'Uruguay de Marcelo Bielsa |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/a-lens-la-cote-divoire-et-guela-doue-eteignent-luruguay-de-marcelo-bielsa |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=SOFOOT.com |language=fr}}</ref>

Doué was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Doué was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Personal life==
Doué's younger brother [[Désiré Doué|Désiré]], and his cousins [[Yann Gboho]], [[Marc-Olivier Doué]], and [[Eddy Doué]] are also professional footballers.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Cassé |first=Josué |date=15 Apr 2022 |title=Rennes : Désiré Doué signe son premier contrat professionnel |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a8278659965667783859-rennes-desire-doue-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel |access-date=2 February 2023 |website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}}}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Lombardi |first=Lorenzo |date=23 October 2022 |title=Attenzione a... Désiré Doué |url=https://www.sottoporta.it/attenzione-a/attenzione-a-desire-doue/ |access-date=2 February 2023}}</ref>

